BLOCKED: target-side Buildroot e1-mmio-smoke transcript is missing.

reason: /usr/bin/e1-mmio-smoke probes the kernel-created platform nodes
  /dev/e1-npu and /sys/bus/platform/drivers/eliza-e1-dma. Those nodes only
  appear when the eliza,e1-npu / eliza,e1-dma platform devices exist in the
  booted device tree and the imported kernel drivers bind to them. No
  available simulation target models the e1 MMIO register blocks at
  E1_DMA_BASE=0x10010000 / E1_NPU_BASE=0x10020000 / E1_DISPLAY_BASE=0x10030000:
  qemu-system-riscv64 -M virt has no eliza,e1 peripherals, and the Renode
  platform (sim/renode/eliza_e1.repl) only models CPU, RAM, UART, PLIC, and
  CLINT. The smoke therefore cannot PASS without e1 silicon, an e1 NPU/DMA
  QEMU device model, or an RTL co-simulation that exposes the register blocks.

required capture command (on a target that exposes /dev/e1-npu):
  E1_SMOKE_CMD='ssh root@TARGET /usr/bin/e1-mmio-smoke' \
    sw/buildroot/scripts/capture-buildroot-evidence.sh /path/to/buildroot smoke

required validation command:
  python3 scripts/check_software_bsp.py buildroot --require-evidence

This marker is not release evidence. Replace it only with a real transcript at
docs/evidence/buildroot/e1-mmio-smoke.log captured from a target or simulator
that actually instantiates the eliza,e1-npu and eliza,e1-dma platform devices.
